   SETN 2024},
Year = {2024},
Note = {13th Hellenic Conference on Artificial Intelligence, Piraeus, GREECE,
   SEP 11-13, 2024},
Abstract = {In 3D design, digital models are created that can be manipulated in
   three dimensions to create realistic representations of objects and
   materials. Educational institutions have been increasing their
   integration of 3D design into fashion programs over the past decade,
   realizing its potential to enhance learning and better prepare students
   for industry demands. By scanning the relevant literature, we discovered
   how 3D design tools are used in fashion education to create detailed
   digital garments, virtual fittings, and realistic renderings. It can be
   argued that fashion education is being transformed by using 3D design
   tools to enhance students' skills and creativity. Prototyping and
   production can be significantly reduced in time and cost thanks to it.
   Promoting sustainable practices and reducing material waste. In a
   nutshell, 3D design integration in fashion education transforms
   traditional teaching methods, offering a more engaging and relevant
   learning experience. Fashion design courses equip students with
   essential skills, encourage innovation, and promote sustainable
   practices.},
